result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 10:07 am cases called- 15CM136 & 15CM203. Defendant Jeffrey E Fritz in court with attorney Scott M Engstrom.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Agreement reached and stated on the record.   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: No Contest to Counts 1 & 2 of 15CM203.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses and reads-in 15CM136. Sentencing argument by ADA Anderson. Sentencing argument by Attorney Engstrom. Statement by defendant. Court sentences the defendant to: SWD and places on probation for a period of 18 months. 1 day credit if revoked. CONDITIONS: No Contact with A. Nelson and/or M. Jackson-Turner. Anger Management Program and follow through. Follow through with any counseling or treatment with Dr. Stephen DalCerro or his treatment successor. Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. Court orders bond on file to be applied. Terms of Agent. Court will allow petition for early termination after 12 months, with recommendation of supervising agent. Appeal Rights Given.
